div.div:
the project goal is to learn more about streaming and RT stream processing and to also test the ELK stack in a full project.
the idea is that it acts as a logging layer for attacks that happen
say we have an automated service that can protect us from most of the attacks
but still vulnerable to 3 types of attacks and also we can act as a DNS filter for some attacks that comes from autorized IP that matches a patern just to add some Regex in the processing :p, so we log all what happen in attack_log and also process the attack events that we are still vulnerable to have a severity and then send it to the attack_alerts and also we send it to the backend so then it wan appear on our frontend dashboard and the imaginary security team can now and go to fix it :)
with some other functionalities and things.
